or Justice is a valuable resource for sociologists and other scholars in the interdisciplinary field of labor studies, as well as for advocates and policymakers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aForeign workersxLabor unionsxOrganizingzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aLabor movementzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aLabor unionsxOrganizingzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aWorking poorzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 4aLabor History. 4aSociology & Social Science. 4aUrban Studies.1 aBloom, Joshua, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMilkman, Ruth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNarro, Victor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080145905440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801459054423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801459054/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-063872-1  DG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles